article.headline: Lafayette 90, Navy 80
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Jamaal Douglas scored 18 points and 17 rebounds, both career highs, and four other Lafayette players were in double figures as the Leopards beat Navy 90-80 on Saturday. Andrei Capusan scored 16 points for Lafayette (5-8, 1-0 Patriot League), while Bilal Abdullah had 15 and Jamaal Hilliard and Sean Knitter each contributed 12. Greg Spink led Navy (4-9, 0-1) with a career-high 22 points and Corey Johnson added 16. Douglas scored 16 of his points in the first half as Lafayette opened up an early 28-16 lead. But Spink scored 10 points in a span of 1:26 to help Navy tie it 38-38 at the half. Navy went ahead 56-55 in the second half on a score by Matt Fannin, but Matt Betley scored with 11:15 remaining to put Lafayette ahead for good. The Leopards made 24 of 28 free throws in the second half and 36 of 44 in the game and also held a 43-38 rebounding edge.
